243
00:15:46,294 --> 00:15:47,335
decisions along the way.

244
00:15:47,355 --> 00:15:52,259
I think we wanted something really dark and moody.

245
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,441
The character who is speaking to the...

246
00:15:56,468 --> 00:16:01,890
player out of a trash can turned into the creature. We needed darkness to put him in, but we didn't.

247
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:06,131
But we wanted him to feel large and scary. And like every time we would make a decision,

248
00:16:06,171 --> 00:16:09,071
the whole game would sort of have to adapt and grow to that decision.

249
00:16:10,712 --> 00:16:14,732
And all along the way, we're just trying to retain, you know, the mood, the feeling,

250
00:16:14,752 --> 00:16:19,053
the camera and the arcadiness that we wanted, hoping that all of those elements would speak

251
00:16:19,073 --> 00:16:25,415
well together and not be, you know, not compete, or that they that they would harmonize.

252
00:16:26,617 --> 00:16:30,942
Um, so it's interesting that you're pointing out like it's arcadey, but also really moody.

253
00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:33,706
Um, hopefully those things work well together.

254
00:16:33,726 --> 00:16:40,795
Uh, but it wasn't really ever a decision to try to mash something disparate with something that wouldn't blend with it, you know.

255
00:16:41,977 --> 00:16:44,879
Right on. That was another hard shot I pulled together.

