00:21:16,714 --> 00:21:19,996
There's kind of an interesting thing you talked about in another interview I was watching.

317
00:21:20,036 --> 00:21:22,377
We were talking about making sure that rooms don't beat themselves.

318
00:21:23,177 --> 00:21:24,178
I thought that was kind of funny.

319
00:21:24,518 --> 00:21:28,841
What's the danger of setting up a room like that and why was it something you wanted to avoid?

320
00:21:29,841 --> 00:21:32,002
Well, I think it just makes for a boring game.

321
00:21:33,003 --> 00:21:37,466
You know, if a player can just bounce the ball and then nothing...

322
00:21:39,247 --> 00:21:40,207
you know, they don't have to do anything.

323
00:21:41,288 --> 00:21:44,670
If the game is in design, if a game is solvable, that's really bad.

324
00:21:45,573 --> 00:21:48,716
Meaning that if there's only one solution to beat it,

325
00:21:49,437 --> 00:21:52,780
and that solution is really clear to the player at the beginning,

326
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:58,045
and there's not a lot of thinking, then it's not as interesting to play, etc.

327
00:21:58,545 --> 00:22:04,150
So a couple of ways we tried to handle that was to make the puzzles activatable,

328
00:22:04,210 --> 00:22:05,271
like I was mentioning before.

329
00:22:05,852 --> 00:22:10,556
There's also a lot of engineering under the hood about how long a ball will bounce

330
00:22:10,596 --> 00:22:11,797
without you interacting with it.

331
00:22:12,513 --> 00:22:16,036
So you'll notice the balls change in color. That's based on the player level.

332
00:22:16,756 --> 00:22:21,361
Makes them more powerful. They'll complete a bumper. They'll fill a bumper with power in less hits.

333
00:22:22,722 --> 00:22:28,667
But if you don't hit them, they'll slowly lose power and then they will only bounce three times.

334
00:22:30,168 --> 00:22:31,029
And then they'll disappear.

335
00:22:31,389 --> 00:22:38,616
So turning the balls into these sort of abstract energy things was a big part of fixing that solvability.

336
00:22:39,647 --> 00:22:45,073
Apologies to the folks at home, we did not get to see that entire puzzle because unfortunately

337
00:22:46,354 --> 00:22:52,621
this is a great game with some particles moving very quickly across the screen, which means

